media.headline: Solarte brings home Jankowski
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Solarte opens the scoring with RBI single
media.bigblurb: Yangervis Solarte rips a single into center field and Travis Jankowski comes in to score, giving the Padres an early 1-0 lead in the 1st

media.headline: Solarte's towering home run
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Solarte launches a solo homer to right-center
media.bigblurb: Yangervis Solarte jumps on a 2-1 pitch and lifts a towering solo home run over the wall in right-center in the top of the 3rd

media.headline: Puig's tough grab on the run
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Puig hustles to snare a fly ball in right
media.bigblurb: Manuel Margot hits a fly ball down the line in right and Yasiel Puig covers a lot of ground to make a nice catch in the 3rd

media.team: San Diego Padres Los Angeles Dodgers
media.headline: Turner not hit by the pitch
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Turner stays at the plate after call stands
media.bigblurb: The Dodgers use a challenge to see if Justin Turner is hit by a pitch, but the call on the field stands after review in the 6th

media.headline: Myers plates Margot
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Myers extends the lead with an RBI single
media.bigblurb: Wil Myers sends a line drive the opposite way into right field to bring home Manuel Margot and increase the Padres' lead to 4-0 in the 8th

media.headline: Turner begins double play
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Turner starts a nifty 5-4-3 double play
media.bigblurb: Justin Turner corrals a ground ball and throws over to second, starting a nice 5-4-3 double play in the top of the 8th

media.headline: Statcast: Puig's dashing grab
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Puig runs 89 feet for grab along foul line
media.bigblurb: Dodgers outfielder Yasiel Puig runs 89 feet in right field to make a catch only made 35% of the time around the foul line

media.headline: Hand gets the final out
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Hand seals the shutout for the Padres
media.bigblurb: Brad Hand forces Justin Turner to ground out to short for the final out in a 4-0 win for the Padres over the Dodgers

media.headline: Update on Urias
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Dodgers give update on Urias' status
media.bigblurb: Julio Urias is optioned to Class A Rancho Cucamonga, but is expected to make his 2017 debut with Triple-A Oklahoma City

media.headline: Richard's scoreless start
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Richard fans five in scoreless start
media.bigblurb: Clayton Richard strikes out five over eight scoreless innings, benefiting from four double plays in the Padres' 4-0 shutout win

media.headline: Seager receives Silver Slugger
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Seager presented with Silver Slugger Award
media.bigblurb: Corey Seager is presented with his 2016 National League Shortstop Silver Slugger Award prior to the Dodgers' 2017 home opener

media.headline: Forsythe begins a double play
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Forsythe starts a double play in the 5th
media.bigblurb: Logan Forsythe picks up Wil Myers' ground ball, steps on second and throws to first in time to turn the double play in the 5th

media.headline: Maeda fans Myers
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Maeda gets Myers to go down swinging
media.bigblurb: Kenta Maeda picks up his first strikeout of the 2017 season as he gets Wil Myers to go down swinging in the top of the 3rd

media.headline: Schimpf brings in Myers
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Schimpf plates Myers with a sacrifice fly
media.bigblurb: Ryan Schimpf lifts a fly ball down the line in left that is deep enough to bring home Wil Myers, doubling the Padres' early lead to 2-0

media.headline: Aybar starts another Padres DP
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Aybar begins a quick double play in the 6th
media.bigblurb: Erick Aybar picks up a chopper and flips over to second to induce a 6-4-3 double play to end the 6th inning

media.blurb: SD@LAD: Richard talks about his strong season debut
media.bigblurb: Clayton Richard talks about his impressive 2017 debut in which he tossed eight scoreless innings against the Dodgers and struck out five

media.headline: Green on win over Dodgers
media.blurb: SD@LAD: Green on Richard's effective start in win
media.bigblurb: Padres manager Andy Green discusses Clayton Richard's effective night on the mound in his team's win over the Dodgers

media.blurb: SD@LAD: Roberts on Maeda, facing Richard in loss
media.bigblurb: Dodgers manager Dave Roberts talks about some hard luck for Kenta Maeda and facing Clayton Richard in a 4-0 loss to the Padres

media.blurb: 4/4/17: Richard, Solarte power Padres to 4-0 win
media.bigblurb: Daily Recap: Yangervis Solarte clubbed a home run and drove in two runs to back a scoreless eight-inning performance from Clayton Richard
